350 more were deported to Auschwitz in early 1944. Mrs. Neufeld and, as she will later reveal, her husband, who had been sent to Belsen with her, were among the several hundred who remained in the camp. Just why they were spared is unknown.</span><sup><a href="#note_18">18</a></sup></note></span>
